            {
              "type": "MathBlock",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\displaystyle\\widetilde{\\Pi}_{i}(\\mathbf{P},P_{E})=\\max_{\\tilde{\\mathbf{q}}_{i%\n},\\tilde{E}_{i}}\\Bigg{\\{}P_{i}F_{i}(\\tilde{\\mathbf{q}}_{i},\\tilde{E}_{i},1)-%\n\\sum_{j=1}^{N}P_{j}\\tilde{q}_{ij}-P_{E}\\tilde{E}_{i}\\Bigg{\\}}."
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Emphasis",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "value": {
                        "string": "Moreover, if "
                      }
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "MathInline",
                      "code": {
                        "string": "W_{i}"
                      },
                      "mathLanguage": "latex",
                      "mathml": "redacted"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "value": {
                        "string": " is strictly convex and differentiable, the optimal input vector "
                      }
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "MathInline",
                      "code": {
                        "string": "(\\mathbf{q}^{*}_{i},E^{*}_{i},L^{*}_{i})"
                      },
                      "mathLanguage": "latex",
                      "mathml": "redacted"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "value": {
                        "string": " is given by"
                      }
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "MathBlock",
              "code": {
                "string": "L^{*}_{i}=(W^{\\prime}_{i})^{-1}\\big{(}\\widetilde{\\Pi}_{i}(\\mathbf{P},P_{E})%\n\\big{)},\\quad q^{*}_{ij}=\\tilde{q}^{*}_{ij}L^{*}_{i}\\quad\\text{for }j=1,\\dots,%\nN,\\quad E^{*}_{i}=\\tilde{E}^{*}_{i}L^{*}_{i}."
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "The function "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\widetilde{\\Pi}_{i}(\\mathbf{P},P_{E})"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " admits a natural economic interpretation: it represents the maximum profit per unit of labor, before deducting labor costs. For CES production technologies, this quantity can be computed explicitly."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Claim",
          "claimType": "Proposition",
          "label": "2.8",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Emphasis",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "value": {
                        "string": "Assume the production function takes the CES form:"
                      }
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "MathBlock",
              "code": {
                "string": "F_{i}(\\mathbf{q}_{i},E_{i},L_{i})=A_{i}\\left(\\sum_{j=1}^{N}\\alpha_{ij}q_{ij}^{%\n-\\rho_{i}}+\\alpha_{iE}E_{i}^{-\\rho_{i}}+\\alpha_{iL}L_{i}^{-\\rho_{i}}\\right)^{-%\n\\frac{1}{\\rho_{i}}},\\quad\\text{with }\\rho_{i}>0."
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Emphasis",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "value": {
                        "string": "Then the optimal normalized input vector "
                      }
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "MathInline",
                      "code": {
                        "string": "(\\tilde{\\mathbf{q}}^{*}_{i},\\tilde{E}^{*}_{i})"
                      },
                      "mathLanguage": "latex",
                      "mathml": "redacted"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "value": {
                        "string": " is given as follows:"
                      }
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "List",
              "items": [
                {
                  "type": "ListItem",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "type": "Paragraph",
                      "content": []
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Paragraph",
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "type": "Emphasis",
                          "content": [
                            {
                              "type": "Text",
                              "value": {
                                "string": "If"
                              }
                            }
                          ]
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "MathBlock",
                      "code": {
                        "string": "\\sum_{j=1}^{N}\\left(\\frac{P_{j}\\alpha_{ij}^{1/\\rho_{i}}}{A_{i}P_{i}}\\right)^{%\n\\frac{\\rho_{i}}{\\rho_{i}+1}}+\\left(\\frac{P_{E}\\alpha_{iE}^{1/\\rho_{i}}}{A_{i}P%\n_{i}}\\right)^{\\frac{\\rho_{i}}{\\rho_{i}+1}}\\leq 1,"
                      },
                      "mathLanguage": "latex",
                      "mathml": "redacted"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Paragraph",
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "type": "Emphasis",
                          "content": [
                            {
                              "type": "Text",
                              "value": {
                                "string": "then the optimal production per unit of labor, "
                              }
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "MathInline",
                          "code": {
                            "string": "\\tilde{Q}^{*}_{i}\\coloneqq F_{i}(\\tilde{\\mathbf{q}}^{*}_{i},\\tilde{E}^{*}_{i},1)"
                          },
                          "mathLanguage": "latex",
                          "mathml": "redacted"
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "Emphasis",
                          "content": [
                            {
                              "type": "Text",
                              "value": {
                                "string": ", is given by"
                              }
                            }
                          ]
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "MathBlock",
                      "code": {
                        "string": "\\tilde{Q}^{*}_{i}=A_{i}\\alpha_{iL}^{-1/\\rho_{i}}\\left(1-\\sum_{j=1}^{N}\\left(%\n\\frac{P_{j}\\alpha_{ij}^{1/\\rho_{i}}}{A_{i}P_{i}}\\right)^{\\frac{\\rho_{i}}{\\rho_%\n{i}+1}}-\\left(\\frac{P_{E}\\alpha_{iE}^{1/\\rho_{i}}}{A_{i}P_{i}}\\right)^{\\frac{%\n\\rho_{i}}{\\rho_{i}+1}}\\right)^{\\frac{1}{\\rho_{i}}}."
                      },
                      "mathLanguage": "latex",
                      "mathml": "redacted"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Paragraph",
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "type": "Emphasis",
                          "content": [
                            {
                              "type": "Text",
                              "value": {
                                "string": "The corresponding optimal inputs are"
                              }
                            }
                          ]
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "MathBlock",
                      "code": {
                        "string": "\\tilde{q}^{*}_{ij}=\\tilde{Q}^{*}_{i}\\left(\\frac{P_{j}A_{i}^{\\rho_{i}}}{P_{i}%\n\\alpha_{ij}}\\right)^{-\\frac{1}{\\rho_{i}+1}},\\qquad\\tilde{E}^{*}_{i}=\\tilde{Q}^%\n{*}_{i}\\left(\\frac{P_{E}A_{i}^{\\rho_{i}}}{P_{i}\\alpha_{iE}}\\right)^{-\\frac{1}{%\n\\rho_{i}+1}}."
                      },
                      "mathLanguage": "latex",
                      "mathml": "redacted"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Paragraph",
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "type": "Emphasis",
                          "content": [
                            {
                              "type": "Text",
                              "value": {
                                "string": "In this case, the maximum profit per unit of labor is"
                              }
                            }
                          ]
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "MathBlock",
                      "code": {
                        "string": "\\widetilde{\\Pi}_{i}(\\mathbf{P},P_{E})=P_{i}A_{i}\\alpha_{iL}^{-1/\\rho_{i}}\\left%\n(1-\\sum_{j=1}^{N}\\left(\\frac{P_{j}\\alpha_{ij}^{1/\\rho_{i}}}{A_{i}P_{i}}\\right)%\n^{\\frac{\\rho_{i}}{\\rho_{i}+1}}-\\left(\\frac{P_{E}\\alpha_{iE}^{1/\\rho_{i}}}{A_{i%\n}P_{i}}\\right)^{\\frac{\\rho_{i}}{\\rho_{i}+1}}\\right)^{\\frac{\\rho_{i}+1}{\\rho_{i%\n}}}."
                      },
                      "mathLanguage": "latex",
                      "mathml": "redacted"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "ListItem",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "type": "Paragraph",
                      "content": []
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Paragraph",
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "type": "Emphasis",
                          "content": [
                            {
                              "type": "Text",
                              "value": {
                                "string": "Otherwise, the optimum is attained at "
                              }
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "MathInline",
                          "code": {
                            "string": "\\tilde{q}^{*}_{ij}=0"
                          },
                          "mathLanguage": "latex",
                          "mathml": "redacted"
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "Emphasis",
                          "content": [
                            {
                              "type": "Text",
                              "value": {
                                "string": " for all "
                              }
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "MathInline",
                          "code": {
                            "string": "j=1,\\dots,N"
                          },
                          "mathLanguage": "latex",
                          "mathml": "redacted"
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "Emphasis",
                          "content": [
                            {
                              "type": "Text",
                              "value": {
                                "string": ", "
                              }
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "MathInline",
                          "code": {
                            "string": "\\tilde{E}^{*}_{i}=0"
                          },
                          "mathLanguage": "latex",
                          "mathml": "redacted"
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "Emphasis",
                          "content": [
                            {
                              "type": "Text",
                              "value": {
                                "string": ", and the resulting optimal production is "
                              }
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "MathInline",
                          "code": {
                            "string": "\\tilde{Q}^{*}_{i}=0"
                          },
                          "mathLanguage": "latex",
                          "mathml": "redacted"
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "Emphasis",
                          "content": [
                            {
                              "type": "Text",
                              "value": {
                                "string": "."
                              }
                            }
                          ]
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              "order": "Unordered"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "Proposition ("
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "Link",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": "2.7"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "target": "S2.Thmtheorem7",
              "title": "Proposition 2.7. ‣ 2.2. Firm’s profit maximization problem ‣ 2. Firm-level profit maximization with carbon pricing ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ") can then be applied to explicitly compute the optimal profit and the corresponding input allocation, provided the labor cost function admits a known convex conjugate — for instance, the power function in Example "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "Link",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": "2.5"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "target": "S2.Thmtheorem5",
              "title": "Example 2.5 (Power labor cost functions). ‣ 2.2. Firm’s profit maximization problem ‣ 2. Firm-level profit maximization with carbon pricing ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "."
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Heading",
      "label": "3.",
      "level": 1,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "Price formation and competitive equilibrium in the static setting"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "In this section, we develop a static equilibrium model of a productive economy composed of "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "N"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": " sectors, where each sector is represented by a single firm that produces a distinct good. The economy’s price system is determined by imposing market-clearing conditions: the total supply of each good must equal the total demand, which includes both final consumption and intermediate input requirements from all sectors. We then formalize the interaction among firms through the notion of "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "Emphasis",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "competitive equilibrium"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": ", defined as a collection of prices and input allocations such that (i) each firm maximizes its profit given prices, and (ii) all markets clear."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "We establish the existence of such a competitive equilibrium by characterizing it as the saddle point of a central planner’s minimax problem. This variational formulation provides an economic interpretation aligned with the First Fundamental Theorem of Welfare Economics, emphasizing the efficiency of equilibrium allocations."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "Each sector faces external demand from consumers and may also compete with an external source of supply. To model this, we introduce sector-specific net demand functions "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "D_{i}:\\mathbb{R}_{\\geq 0}\\to\\mathbb{R}"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": ", where "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "D_{i}(P)"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": " denotes the difference between external demand and external supply for the "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "i"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "-th sector at a given price "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "P\\geq 0"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": ". These functions may take both positive and negative values and are assumed to satisfy the following conditions."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Claim",
      "claimType": "Theorem",
      "label": "3.1",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "For every "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "i=1,\\dots,N"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ", the net demand function "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "D_{i}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " is strictly decreasing and continuous on "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\mathbb{R}_{&gt;0}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ". Moreover, it satisfies the following asymptotic conditions:"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "\\lim_{P\\to 0}D_{i}(P)=\\infty,\\quad\\lim_{P\\to\\infty}D_{i}(P)\\leq 0."
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "This assumption encompasses both a closed economy without exogenous supply and an open economy with external supply. In the closed economy case, we have "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "D_{i}(P)&gt;0"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": " for all "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "P\\geq 0"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": ", and the limiting value as the price tends to infinity approaches zero."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Claim",
      "claimType": "Theorem",
      "label": "3.2",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "The following examples illustrate modifications of the standard power demand function that account for the presence of external supply, while satisfying Assumption "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "Link",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": "3.1"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "target": "S3.Thmtheorem1",
              "title": "Assumption 3.1 (Properties of net demand functions). ‣ 3. Price formation and competitive equilibrium in the static setting ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "A first class of net demand functions is given by:"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "D_{i}(P)=a_{i}P^{-\\epsilon_{i}}-b_{i},\\quad\\text{with }a_{i},\\epsilon_{i}>0,%\n\\quad b_{i}\\geq 0,"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "where the first term models consumer demand with elasticity "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\epsilon_{i}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ", and the constant term "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "b_{i}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " represents a finite external supply."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "A second variant incorporates a price-dependent external supply:"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "D_{i}(P)=a_{i}P^{-\\epsilon_{i}}-b_{i}P^{\\delta_{i}},\\quad\\text{with }a_{i},%\n\\epsilon_{i},\\delta_{i}>0,\\quad b_{i}\\geq 0."
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "Here, the external supply grows unboundedly with the price, so that the net demand diverges to "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "-\\infty"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " as "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "P\\to\\infty"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "In both cases, the closed economy scenario with no external supply is recovered by setting "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "b_{i}=0"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "."
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "Let "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "{\\mathcal{Q}}=(q_{ij})_{i,j=1,\\dots,N}"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": " represent the matrix of quantities exchanged among companies. Using this notation, we define an allocation matrix "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "({\\mathcal{Q}},\\mathbf{E},\\mathbf{L})\\in\\mathbb{R}^{N(N+2)}"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "Under the assumption of no market frictions, the price vector must satisfy the following market clearing condition:"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "MathBlock",
      "code": {
        "string": "F_{i}(\\mathbf{q}_{i},E_{i},L_{i})=D_{i}(P_{i})+\\sum^{N}_{j=1}q_{ji},\\quad i=1,%\n\\dots,N."
      },
      "mathLanguage": "latex",
      "mathml": "redacted"
    },
    {
      "type": "Paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "for any fixed "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "({\\mathcal{Q}},\\mathbf{E},\\mathbf{L})\\in\\mathbb{R}^{N(N+2)}"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "The left-hand side of the equation represents the total endogenous supply of good "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "i"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": ", which equals the output of sector "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "i"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": ". The right-hand side represents the total net demand for good "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "i"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": ", comprising two components: the exogenous net demand, driven by the demand function "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "D_{i}"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": ", and the endogenous or intermediate demand, which reflects the quantity of good "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "i"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": " demanded by all sectors, including sector "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "i"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": " itself."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "We now introduce the notion of competitive equilibrium within our framework."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Claim",
      "claimType": "Theorem",
      "label": "3.3",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "A competitive equilibrium (CE) is a vector "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "(\\mathbf{P}^{*},{\\mathcal{Q}}^{*},\\mathbf{E}^{*},\\mathbf{L}^{*})\\in\\mathbb{R}^%\n{N}_{\\geq 0}\\times\\mathbb{R}^{N(N+2)}_{\\geq 0}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " of prices and inputs such that, for each "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "i=1,\\dots,N"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ":"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "List",
          "items": [
            {
              "type": "ListItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Paragraph",
                  "content": []
                },
                {
                  "type": "Paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "value": {
                        "string": "The price "
                      }
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "MathInline",
                      "code": {
                        "string": "P^{*,i}"
                      },
                      "mathLanguage": "latex",
                      "mathml": "redacted"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "value": {
                        "string": " satisfies the market clearing condition ("
                      }
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Link",
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "type": "Text",
                          "value": {
                            "string": "8"
                          }
                        }
                      ],
                      "target": "S3.E8",
                      "title": "In 3. Price formation and competitive equilibrium in the static setting ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "value": {
                        "string": ")."
                      }
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "ListItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Paragraph",
                  "content": []
                },
                {
                  "type": "Paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "value": {
                        "string": "The input vector "
                      }
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "MathInline",
                      "code": {
                        "string": "(\\mathbf{q}^{*}_{i},E^{*}_{i},L^{*}_{i})"
                      },
                      "mathLanguage": "latex",
                      "mathml": "redacted"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "value": {
                        "string": " solves the profit maximization problem ("
                      }
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Link",
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "type": "Text",
                          "value": {
                            "string": "5"
                          }
                        }
                      ],
                      "target": "S2.E5",
                      "title": "In 2.2. Firm’s profit maximization problem ‣ 2. Firm-level profit maximization with carbon pricing ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "value": {
                        "string": ")."
                      }
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "order": "Unordered"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "To establish the existence of a CE, we consider the following minimax problem:"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "MathBlock",
      "code": {
        "string": "\\min_{\\mathbf{P}}\\sum^{N}_{i=1}\\max_{\\mathbf{q}_{i},E_{i},L_{i}}\\Bigg{\\{}P_{i}%\nF_{i}(\\mathbf{q}_{i},E_{i},L_{i})-\\sum^{N}_{j=1}P_{j}q_{ij}-P_{E}E_{i}-W_{i}(L%\n_{i})-\\Delta_{i}(P_{i})\\Bigg{\\}},"
      },
      "mathLanguage": "latex",
      "mathml": "redacted"
    },
    {
      "type": "Paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "where "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "\\Delta_{i}(P)\\coloneqq\\int^{P}_{1}D_{i}(z)\\,dz"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": " denotes the consumer surplus function of sector "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "i"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": " up to a given price "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "P\\geq 0"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "By interchanging the summation and maximization operators, we reformulate Problem ("
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "Link",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "9"
              }
            }
          ],
          "target": "S3.E9",
          "title": "In 3. Price formation and competitive equilibrium in the static setting ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": ") as:"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "MathBlock",
      "code": {
        "string": "\\min_{\\mathbf{P}}\\max_{{\\mathcal{Q}},\\mathbf{E},\\mathbf{L}}{\\mathcal{L}}(%\n\\mathbf{P},{\\mathcal{Q}},\\mathbf{E},\\mathbf{L}),"
      },
      "mathLanguage": "latex",
      "mathml": "redacted"
    },
    {
      "type": "Paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "where "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "{\\mathcal{L}}:\\mathbb{R}^{N}_{\\geq 0}\\times\\mathbb{R}^{N(N+2)}\\to\\mathbb{R}"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": " is the Lagrangian function defined by:"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "MathBlock",
      "code": {
        "string": "{\\mathcal{L}}(\\mathbf{P},{\\mathcal{Q}},\\mathbf{E},\\mathbf{L})\\coloneqq\\sum^{N}%\n_{i=1}\\Bigg{\\{}P_{i}F_{i}(\\mathbf{q}_{i},E_{i},L_{i})-\\sum^{N}_{j=1}P_{j}q_{ij%\n}-P_{E}E_{i}-W_{i}(L_{i})-\\Delta_{i}(P_{i})\\Bigg{\\}}."
      },
      "mathLanguage": "latex",
      "mathml": "redacted"
    },
    {
      "type": "Paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "The Lagrangian function captures the total surplus of the economy: it aggregates firms’ profits while subtracting the consumer surplus terms "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "\\Delta_{i}(P_{i})"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": ", which appear with a negative sign to reflect that consumers only demand goods in this model and do not share in firms’ profits."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Claim",
      "claimType": "Theorem",
      "label": "3.4",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "Under Assumption "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "Link",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": "3.1"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "target": "S3.Thmtheorem1",
              "title": "Assumption 3.1 (Properties of net demand functions). ‣ 3. Price formation and competitive equilibrium in the static setting ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ", the consumer surplus functions "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\Delta_{i}:\\mathbb{R}_{\\geq 0}\\to\\mathbb{R}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " are well-defined for all non-negative prices, with the convention:"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "\\Delta_{i}(P)=-\\int^{1}_{P}D_{i}(z)\\,dz,\\quad\\text{for all $P\\leq 1$}."
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "In particular, "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\lim_{P\\to 0^{+}}\\Delta_{i}(P)"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " exists, though it may equal "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "-\\infty"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ". Consequently, "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\Delta_{i}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " is upper semi-continuous over "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\mathbb{R}_{\\geq 0}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "Additionally, since the demand functions "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "D_{i}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " are continuous on "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\mathbb{R}_{&gt;0}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ", each consumer surplus function "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\Delta_{i}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " is continuously differentiable on this domain."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "Finally, because each demand function "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "D_{i}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " is strictly decreasing, the consumer surplus functions "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\Delta_{i}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " are strictly concave."
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "From standard convex analysis (see, e.g., "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "Citation",
          "target": "bib.bib34",
          "citationMode": "Narrative",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "Ekeland and Témam, 1999, Ch. 6"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "), the following inequality holds:"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "MathBlock",
      "code": {
        "string": "\\sup_{{\\mathcal{Q}},\\mathbf{E},\\mathbf{L}}\\inf_{\\mathbf{P}}{\\mathcal{L}}(%\n\\mathbf{P},{\\mathcal{Q}},\\mathbf{E},\\mathbf{L})\\leq\\inf_{\\mathbf{P}}\\sup_{{%\n\\mathcal{Q}},\\mathbf{E},\\mathbf{L}}{\\mathcal{L}}(\\mathbf{P},{\\mathcal{Q}},%\n\\mathbf{E},\\mathbf{L}),"
      },
      "mathLanguage": "latex",
      "mathml": "redacted"
    },
    {
      "type": "Paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "with strict inequality generally occurring. The right-hand side corresponds to the competitive equilibrium formulation, where each agent optimizes its own objective given prevailing market prices and the decisions of other agents. In contrast, the left-hand side — corresponding to the minimax problem ("
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "Link",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "10"
              }
            }
          ],
          "target": "S3.E10",
          "title": "In 3. Price formation and competitive equilibrium in the static setting ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": ") — reflects the perspective of a central planner who simultaneously allocates inputs and sets prices in order to maximize total economic surplus, as represented by the Lagrangian ("
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "Link",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "11"
              }
            }
          ],
          "target": "S3.E11",
          "title": "In 3. Price formation and competitive equilibrium in the static setting ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": ")."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "We now recall the following well-known definition, tailored to our context."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Claim",
      "claimType": "Theorem",
      "label": "3.5",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "A vector "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "(\\mathbf{P}^{*},{\\mathcal{Q}}^{*},\\mathbf{E}^{*},\\mathbf{L}^{*})\\in\\mathbb{R}^%\n{N}_{\\geq 0}\\times\\mathbb{R}^{N(N+2)}_{\\geq 0}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " is called a saddle point of "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "{\\mathcal{L}}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " on "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\mathbb{R}^{N}_{\\geq 0}\\times\\mathbb{R}^{N(N+2)}_{\\geq 0}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " if:"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "{\\mathcal{L}}(\\mathbf{P}^{*},{\\mathcal{Q}},\\mathbf{E},\\mathbf{L})\\leq{\\mathcal%\n{L}}(\\mathbf{P}^{*},{\\mathcal{Q}}^{*},\\mathbf{E}^{*},\\mathbf{L}^{*})\\leq{%\n\\mathcal{L}}(\\mathbf{P},{\\mathcal{Q}}^{*},\\mathbf{E}^{*},\\mathbf{L}^{*})"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "for all "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\mathbf{P}\\in\\mathbb{R}^{N}_{\\geq 0}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " and "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "({\\mathcal{Q}},\\mathbf{E},\\mathbf{L})\\in\\mathbb{R}^{N(N+2)}_{\\geq 0}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "In particular, a vector "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "(\\mathbf{P}^{*},{\\mathcal{Q}}^{*},\\mathbf{E}^{*},\\mathbf{L}^{*})"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " is a saddle point if and only if satisfies the Minimax equality:"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "{\\mathcal{L}}(\\mathbf{P}^{*},{\\mathcal{Q}}^{*},\\mathbf{E}^{*},\\mathbf{L}^{*})=%\n\\max_{{\\mathcal{Q}},\\mathbf{E},\\mathbf{L}}\\min_{\\mathbf{P}}{\\mathcal{L}}(%\n\\mathbf{P},{\\mathcal{Q}},\\mathbf{E},\\mathbf{L})=\\min_{\\mathbf{P}}\\max_{{%\n\\mathcal{Q}},\\mathbf{E},\\mathbf{L}}{\\mathcal{L}}(\\mathbf{P},{\\mathcal{Q}},%\n\\mathbf{E},\\mathbf{L})."
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "The following lemma establishes a link between the notion of a saddle point of "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "\\mathcal{L}"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": " and competitive equilibrium. The proof is provided in Appendix "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "Link",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "B"
              }
            }
          ],
          "target": "A2",
          "title": "Appendix B Proof of Lemma 3.6 ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Claim",
      "claimType": "Lemma",
      "label": "3.6",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Emphasis",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": "Suppose that Assumptions "
                  }
                },
                {
                  "type": "Link",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "value": {
                        "string": "3.1"
                      }
                    }
                  ],
                  "target": "S3.Thmtheorem1",
                  "title": "Assumption 3.1 (Properties of net demand functions). ‣ 3. Price formation and competitive equilibrium in the static setting ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
                },
                {
