              ],
              "target": "S3.Thmtheorem6",
              "title": "Lemma 3.6. ‣ 3. Price formation and competitive equilibrium in the static setting ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ", establishing the existence and uniqueness of a CE is equivalent to proving the existence and uniqueness of a saddle point for "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "{\\mathcal{L}}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " on "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\mathbb{R}^{N}_{&gt;0}\\times\\mathbb{R}^{N(N+2)}_{\\geq 0}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ". To this end, we verify the assumptions of the minimax theorem (see Proposition VI.2.4 in "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "Citation",
              "target": "bib.bib34",
              "citationMode": "Narrative",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
