                    },
                    {
                      "type": "MathInline",
                      "code": {
                        "string": "{\\mathcal{R}}^{i}(m_{0})"
                      },
                      "mathLanguage": "latex",
                      "mathml": "redacted"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "value": {
                        "string": " is weakly"
                      }
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Superscript",
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "type": "Text",
                          "value": {
                            "string": "2"
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Superscript",
                      "content": [
                        {
                          "type": "Text",
                          "value": {
                            "string": "2"
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "value": {
                        "string": "2"
                      }
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "value": {
                        "string": "Here, ’weakly’ refers to compactness with respect to the topology "
                      }
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "MathInline",
                      "code": {
                        "string": "\\tau_{p}\\otimes\\tau_{p}"
                      },
                      "mathLanguage": "latex",
                      "mathml": "redacted"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "value": {
                        "string": "."
                      }
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "value": {
                        "string": " compact in "
                      }
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "MathInline",
                      "code": {
                        "string": "{\\mathcal{V}}_{p}(\\overline{{\\mathcal{O}}}_{i})\\times{\\mathcal{M}}_{p}([0,T]%\n\\times\\overline{{\\mathcal{O}}}_{i})"
                      },
                      "mathLanguage": "latex",
                      "mathml": "redacted"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "Text",
                      "value": {
                        "string": "."
                      }
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "In the linear programming formulation of the optimal stopping problem, the optimization over stopping times is recast as an optimization over occupation flows and exit measures "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "(m^{i},\\mu^{i})"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ". Specifically, the firm’s expected profit maximization problem becomes:"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "\\begin{split}\\max_{(m^{i},\\mu^{i})\\in{\\mathcal{R}}^{i}(m^{i}_{0})}&\\int_{0}^{T%\n}\\int_{\\overline{{\\mathcal{O}}}_{i}}e^{-rt}\\left\\{\\overline{\\Pi}_{i}(\\mathbf{P%\n}(t),P_{E}(t),x)-\\kappa_{i}\\right\\}m^{i}_{t}(dx)\\,dt\\\\\n&-\\int_{0}^{T}\\int_{\\overline{{\\mathcal{O}}}_{i}}K_{i}e^{-(r+\\gamma_{i})t}\\mu^%\n{i}(dt,dx).\\end{split}"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "The connection between the original optimal stopping problem ("
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "Link",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": "21"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "target": "S4.E21",
              "title": "In 4.1. The optimal default problem of the generic firm ‣ 4. Mean-field game approach to a dynamic market model with defaults ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ") and its linear programming counterpart ("
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "Link",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": "23"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "target": "S4.E23",
              "title": "In 4.2. Linear programming formulation ‣ 4. Mean-field game approach to a dynamic market model with defaults ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ") is rigorously established in "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "Citation",
              "target": "bib.bib23",
              "citationMode": "Narrative",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": "Bouveret et al. (2020)"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " and "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "Citation",
              "target": "bib.bib31",
              "citationMode": "Narrative",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": "Dumitrescu et al. (2021)"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ". Specifically, defining the value functional"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "\\displaystyle\\Gamma_{i}(m^{i},\\mu^{i},\\mathbf{P},P_{E})"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "it can be shown, under additional assumptions, that the following identity holds:"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "\\Gamma^{*}_{i}(\\mathbf{P},P_{E})\\coloneqq\\max_{m^{i},\\mu^{i}\\in{\\mathcal{R}}^{%\ni}(m^{i}_{0})}\\Gamma_{i}(m^{i},\\mu^{i},\\mathbf{P},P_{E})=\\int_{{\\mathcal{O}}_{%\ni}}v_{i}(\\mathbf{P},P_{E},x)\\,m^{i}_{0}(dx),"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "where "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "v_{i}(\\mathbf{P},P_{E},x)"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " is the value function previously introduced in the optimal stopping problem ("
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "Link",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": "21"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "target": "S4.E21",
              "title": "In 4.1. The optimal default problem of the generic firm ‣ 4. Mean-field game approach to a dynamic market model with defaults ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ")."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "To complete the linear programming formulation, we specify the mechanism for equilibrium price formation. Analogous to the static model in Section "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "Link",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": "3"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "target": "S3",
              "title": "3. Price formation and competitive equilibrium in the static setting ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ", we introduce time-inhomogeneous net demand functions "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "D_{i}\\colon[0,T]\\times\\mathbb{R}_{\\geq 0}\\to\\mathbb{R}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " for each good "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "i=1,\\dots,N"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ". The value "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "D_{i}(t,P_{i}(t))"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " at time "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "t"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " represents the net external demand for good "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "i"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " at the current time, defined as the difference between external demand and external supply. The time dependence accounts for evolving factors such as population growth or inflation."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "We adopt the following assumption, which mirrors the demand conditions in the static model."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Claim",
          "claimType": "Theorem",
          "label": "4.8",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": "For each "
                  }
                },
                {
                  "type": "MathInline",
                  "code": {
                    "string": "i=1,\\dots,N"
                  },
                  "mathLanguage": "latex",
                  "mathml": "redacted"
                },
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": ", the net demand function "
                  }
                },
                {
                  "type": "MathInline",
                  "code": {
                    "string": "D_{i}"
                  },
                  "mathLanguage": "latex",
                  "mathml": "redacted"
                },
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": " is continuous and strictly decreasing in the price variable. Moreover, it satisfies the limiting behavior:"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "MathBlock",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\lim_{P\\to 0}D_{i}(t,P)=\\infty,\\qquad\\lim_{P\\to\\infty}D_{i}(t,P)\\leq 0,"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": "uniformly in "
                  }
                },
                {
                  "type": "MathInline",
                  "code": {
                    "string": "t\\in[0,T]"
                  },
                  "mathLanguage": "latex",
                  "mathml": "redacted"
                },
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": "."
                  }
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "For each good "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "i=1,\\dots,N"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ", the mean-field market-clearing condition reads:"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "\\int_{\\overline{{\\mathcal{O}}}_{i}}F_{i}(\\mathbf{q}_{i}(t,x),E_{i}(t,x),L_{i}(%\nt,x))\\,m^{i}_{t}(dx)=D_{i}(t,P_{i}(t))+\\sum_{j=1}^{N}\\int_{\\overline{{\\mathcal%\n{O}}}_{i}}q_{ji}(t,x)\\,m^{j}_{t}(dx),"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "for any input matrix function "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "({\\mathcal{Q}},\\mathbf{E},\\mathbf{L})\\colon[0,T]\\times{\\mathcal{O}}_{i}\\to%\n\\mathbb{R}_{\\geq 0}^{N(N+2)}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ", and for any vector of occupation measure flows "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\mathbf{m}\\coloneqq(m^{i})_{i=1,\\dots,N}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "The left-hand side of ("
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "Link",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": "24"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "target": "S4.E24",
              "title": "In 4.2. Linear programming formulation ‣ 4. Mean-field game approach to a dynamic market model with defaults ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ") represents the total endogenous supply of good "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "i"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " from the mean-field firm at time "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "t"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ", computed as the integral of the production function over the distribution of active (non-defaulted) agents. The right-hand side corresponds to the total net demand, including both external and endogenous contributions, again integrated against the current occupation measures."
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Section",
      "sectionType": "Main",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Heading",
          "label": "4.3.",
          "level": 2,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "Linear programming MFG Nash equilibrium"
