              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " introduced in ("
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "Link",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": "6"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "target": "S2.E6",
              "title": "In 2.2. Firm’s profit maximization problem ‣ 2. Firm-level profit maximization with carbon pricing ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "), and "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\widetilde{\\Pi}_{i}(\\mathbf{P},P_{E})"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " is defined as in ("
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "Link",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": "7"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "target": "S2.E7",
              "title": "In Proposition 2.7. ‣ 2.2. Firm’s profit maximization problem ‣ 2. Firm-level profit maximization with carbon pricing ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "). In the second line, we introduced the normalized variables"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "\\tilde{q}_{ij}\\coloneqq\\frac{q_{ij}}{L_{i}},\\quad\\tilde{E}_{i}\\coloneqq\\frac{E%\n_{i}}{L_{i}}."
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "Assuming "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "W_{i}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " is strictly convex and differentiable, the first-order condition for the optimal labor input "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "L^{*}_{i}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " yields"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "W^{\\prime}_{i}(L^{*}_{i})=\\widetilde{\\Pi}_{i}(\\mathbf{P},P_{E})."
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "Since "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "W_{i}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " is strictly convex, its derivative "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "W^{\\prime}_{i}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " is strictly increasing and hence invertible. Solving for "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "L^{*}_{i}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " gives"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "L^{*}_{i}=(W^{\\prime}_{i})^{-1}\\big{(}\\widetilde{\\Pi}_{i}(\\mathbf{P},P_{E})%\n\\big{)}."
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "Finally, given the solution "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\tilde{\\mathbf{q}}^{*}_{i},\\tilde{E}^{*}_{i}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " to problem ("
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "Link",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": "7"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "target": "S2.E7",
              "title": "In Proposition 2.7. ‣ 2.2. Firm’s profit maximization problem ‣ 2. Firm-level profit maximization with carbon pricing ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "), the optimal input quantities and emissions are recovered via the normalized variables:"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "q^{*}_{ij}=\\tilde{q}^{*}_{ij}L^{*}_{i},\\quad j=1,\\dots,N,\\quad E^{*}_{i}=%\n\\tilde{E}^{*}_{i}L^{*}_{i}."
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "This concludes the proof."
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Section",
      "sectionType": "Main",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Heading",
          "label": "A.3.",
          "level": 2,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "Proof of Proposition"
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "2.8"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "Let "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "F_{i}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " denote the CES production function with constant returns to scale and positive substitution parameter "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\rho_{i}&gt;0"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ", given by:"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "F_{i}(\\mathbf{q}_{i},E_{i},L_{i})=A_{i}\\left(\\sum_{j=1}^{N}\\alpha_{ij}q_{ij}^{%\n-\\rho_{i}}+\\alpha_{iE}E_{i}^{-\\rho_{i}}+\\alpha_{iL}L_{i}^{-\\rho_{i}}\\right)^{-%\n\\frac{1}{\\rho_{i}}}."
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "Differentiating the normalized profit with respect to the normalized inputs and emissions yields the first-order conditions:"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "\\displaystyle P_{i}A_{i}^{-\\rho_{i}}F_{i}(\\tilde{\\mathbf{q}}_{i},\\tilde{E}_{i}%\n,1)^{\\rho_{i}+1}\\alpha_{ij}\\tilde{q}_{ij}^{-\\rho_{i}-1}-P_{j}=0,\\quad\\quad j=1%\n,\\dots,N,"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "The left-hand side of each equation is a decreasing function of the corresponding input (i.e., "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\tilde{q}_{ij}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " or "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\tilde{E}_{i}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "), holding all other parameters fixed. Moreover, for "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\rho_{i}&gt;0"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ", the following asymptotic limits hold:"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "\\displaystyle\\lim_{\\tilde{q}_{ij}\\to 0}A_{i}^{-\\rho_{i}}F_{i}(\\tilde{\\mathbf{q%\n}}_{i},\\tilde{E}_{i},1)^{\\rho_{i}+1}\\alpha_{ij}\\tilde{q}_{ij}^{-\\rho_{i}-1}=%\n\\alpha_{ij}^{-1/\\rho_{i}}A_{i},"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "It follows that the optimality conditions are:"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "\\displaystyle P_{i}A_{i}^{-\\rho_{i}}F_{i}(\\tilde{\\mathbf{q}}_{i},\\tilde{E}_{i}%\n,1)^{\\rho_{i}+1}\\alpha_{ij}\\tilde{q}_{ij}^{-\\rho_{i}-1}=P_{j}\\quad\\text{if}%\n\\quad\\frac{P_{j}}{P_{i}}\\leq\\alpha_{ij}^{-1/\\rho_{i}}A_{i},\\quad\\text{and}%\n\\quad\\tilde{q}_{ij}=0\\text{ otherwise},"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "for "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "j=1,\\dots,N"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ", and"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "\\displaystyle P_{i}A_{i}^{-\\rho_{i}}F_{i}(\\tilde{\\mathbf{q}}_{i},\\tilde{E}_{i}%\n,1)^{\\rho_{i}+1}\\alpha_{iE}\\tilde{E}_{i}^{-\\rho_{i}-1}=P_{E}\\quad\\text{if}%\n\\quad\\frac{P_{E}}{P_{i}}\\leq\\alpha_{iE}^{-1/\\rho_{i}}A_{i},\\quad\\text{and}%\n\\quad\\tilde{E}_{i}=0\\text{ otherwise}."
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "It is easy to verify that"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "\\displaystyle\\lim_{\\tilde{q}_{ij}\\to 0^{+}}F_{i}(\\tilde{\\mathbf{q}}_{i},\\tilde%\n{E}_{i},1)=0\\quad\\text{for some }j=1,\\dots,N,"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "so that if "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\tilde{q}_{ij}=0"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " for any "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "j"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ", or "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\tilde{E}_{i}=0"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ", then the total output is zero. In such a scenario, all inputs vanish: "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\tilde{q}_{ij}=0"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " for all "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "j"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ", and "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\tilde{E}_{i}=0"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "The optimality conditions can therefore be summarized as:"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "\\text{if}\\quad\\frac{P_{j}}{P_{i}}\\leq\\alpha_{ij}^{-1/\\rho_{i}}A_{i}\\quad\\text{%\nfor all }j=1,\\dots,N,\\quad\\text{and}\\quad\\frac{P_{E}}{P_{i}}\\leq\\alpha_{iE}^{-%\n1/\\rho_{i}}A_{i},"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "then:"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "P_{i}A_{i}^{-\\rho_{i}}F_{i}(\\tilde{\\mathbf{q}}_{i},\\tilde{E}_{i},1)^{\\rho_{i}+%\n1}\\alpha_{ij}\\tilde{q}_{ij}^{-\\rho_{i}-1}=P_{j},\\quad\\text{for all }j=1,\\dots,N,"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "and:"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "P_{i}A_{i}^{-\\rho_{i}}F_{i}(\\tilde{\\mathbf{q}}_{i},\\tilde{E}_{i},1)^{\\rho_{i}+%\n1}\\alpha_{iE}\\tilde{E}_{i}^{-\\rho_{i}-1}=P_{E}."
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "Otherwise, we have "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\tilde{q}_{ij}=0"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " for all "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "j"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ", and "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\tilde{E}_{i}=0"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "To obtain the explicit expressions, suppose the above condition is satisfied, and denote by "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\tilde{Q}^{*}_{i}:=F_{i}(\\tilde{\\mathbf{q}}^{*}_{i},\\tilde{E}^{*}_{i},1)"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " the optimal production normalized by labor. Then the optimal inputs are:"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "\\displaystyle\\tilde{q}^{*}_{ij}=\\tilde{Q}^{*}_{i}\\left(\\frac{P_{j}A_{i}^{\\rho_%\n{i}}}{P_{i}\\alpha_{ij}}\\right)^{-\\frac{1}{\\rho_{i}+1}},\\quad\\tilde{E}^{*}_{i}=%\n\\tilde{Q}^{*}_{i}\\left(\\frac{P_{E}A_{i}^{\\rho_{i}}}{P_{i}\\alpha_{iE}}\\right)^{%\n-\\frac{1}{\\rho_{i}+1}}."
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "Substituting these into "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "F_{i}(\\tilde{\\mathbf{q}}^{*}_{i},\\tilde{E}^{*}_{i},1)"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ", we obtain the optimal normalized output:"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "\\displaystyle\\tilde{Q}^{*}_{i}=A_{i}\\alpha_{iL}^{-\\frac{1}{\\rho_{i}}}\\left(1-%\n\\sum_{j=1}^{N}\\left(\\frac{P_{j}\\alpha_{ij}^{1/\\rho_{i}}}{A_{i}P_{i}}\\right)^{%\n\\frac{\\rho_{i}}{\\rho_{i}+1}}-\\left(\\frac{P_{E}\\alpha_{iE}^{1/\\rho_{i}}}{A_{i}P%\n_{i}}\\right)^{\\frac{\\rho_{i}}{\\rho_{i}+1}}\\right)^{\\frac{1}{\\rho_{i}}}."
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "This expression is valid whenever the term inside the parentheses is non-negative; otherwise, the optimal production is zero."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "Thus, the optimal production and inputs are given by ("
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "Link",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": "43"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "target": "A1.E43",
              "title": "In A.3. Proof of Proposition 2.8 ‣ Appendix A Proofs of results from Section 2 ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": ") and ("
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "Link",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "value": {
                    "string": "42"
                  }
                }
              ],
              "target": "A1.E42",
              "title": "In A.3. Proof of Proposition 2.8 ‣ Appendix A Proofs of results from Section 2 ‣ Propagation of carbon price shocks through the value chain: the mean-field game of defaults"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "), respectively, if and only if"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "\\sum_{j=1}^{N}\\left(\\frac{P_{j}\\alpha_{ij}^{1/\\rho_{i}}}{A_{i}P_{i}}\\right)^{%\n\\frac{\\rho_{i}}{\\rho_{i}+1}}+\\left(\\frac{P_{E}\\alpha_{iE}^{1/\\rho_{i}}}{A_{i}P%\n_{i}}\\right)^{\\frac{\\rho_{i}}{\\rho_{i}+1}}\\leq 1;"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "otherwise, both production and input levels are zero."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "Under the condition of strictly positive production, the normalized profit function "
              }
            },
            {
              "type": "MathInline",
              "code": {
                "string": "\\widetilde{\\Pi}_{i}"
              },
              "mathLanguage": "latex",
              "mathml": "redacted"
            },
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": " is given by:"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "MathBlock",
          "code": {
            "string": "\\displaystyle\\widetilde{\\Pi}_{i}(\\mathbf{P},P_{E})"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "This concludes the proof."
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Heading",
      "label": "Appendix B",
      "level": 2,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "Proof of Lemma"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "3.6"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": "Let "
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "MathInline",
          "code": {
            "string": "(\\mathbf{P}^{*},{\\mathcal{Q}}^{*},\\mathbf{E}^{*},\\mathbf{L}^{*})\\in\\mathbb{R}^%\n{N}_{&gt;0}\\times\\mathbb{R}^{N(N+2)}_{\\geq 0}"
          },
          "mathLanguage": "latex",
          "mathml": "redacted"
        },
        {
          "type": "Text",
          "value": {
            "string": " be a saddle point of the Lagrangian defined by ("
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "Link",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "Text",
              "value": {
                "string": "11"
              }
